<section xml:id="intro-sec-argue">
    <title>Invitation to Discover "Why" </title>
    <!--Might move into chapter on area near area formulas assignment-->
    

    <exploration>
      <task>
      <statement>
        <p> Compute the following sums?
          <ol>
            <li>
              <p>
                <m>1+3</m>
              </p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <m>1+3+5</m>
            </li>
            <li>
              <m>1+3+5+7</m>
            </li>
            <li>
              <m>1+3+5+7+9</m>
            </li>
          </ol> 
        </p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task>
      <statement>
        <p>
          Without actually adding the values, make a prediction for the 
          following sums:
          <ol>
            <li>
              <m>1+3+5+\cdots +11</m>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p>
                <m>1+3+5+\cdots + 41</m>
              </p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <m>1+3+5+\cdots +201</m>
            </li>
          </ol>
        </p>
      </statement>
      <hint>
        <p>
          The expression <m>1+3+5+\cdots + 11</m> is another way of writing 
          <m>1+3+5+7+9+11</m>. We write enough addends to establish a pattern  
          and then the <m>\cdots </m> tells the reader that the pattern continues.
          The <m>+11</m> at the end indicates that the sum will end when the pattern 
          reaches <m>11</m>. 
        </p>
      </hint>
    </task>
    </exploration>
      
  </section>